mple of a distinction  which demeans the individual and strengthens and perpetrates [sic] the view that gays  and lesbians are less worthy of protection as individuals in Canada’s society.  The  potential harm to the dignity and perceived worth of gay and lesbian individuals  constitutes a particularly cruel form of discrimination.”     These observations were made in the context of discrimination on grounds of sexual  orientation in the employment field and would apply with even greater force to the  criminalisation of consensual sodomy in private between adult males.      29 Norris v Republic of Ireland (1991) 13 EHRR 186 at 192 para 21 quoting with approval the finding of an  Irish judge.  30 Above n 27 per Cory J at para 102.','N'),(308,118,1,34,'CANADA|CANADIAN',101,'SUPREME COURT OF CANADA','supreme court of canada',NULL,-1,26,'supreme court of canada','N'),(308,119,2,-1,'IC',15,'European Court of Human Rights','European Court of Human Rights',NULL,-1,26,'European Court of Human Rights','N'),(308,120,1,172,'South Africa|South African',451,'Constitutional Court','1995 (3) SA 391 (CC)',NULL,34,28,'34 S v Makwanyane and Another 1995 (6) BCLR 665 (CC);  1995 (3) SA 391 (CC) at paras 328-330;  Hugo  above n 17 at para 41;  Prinsloo above n 17 at paras 31-33;  Ferreira v Levin NO and Others 1996 (1)  BCLR 1 (CC);  1996 (1) SA 984 (CC).','N'),(308,121,1,172,'South Africa|South African',451,'Constitutional Court','1996 (1) SA 984 (CC)',NULL,34,28,'34 S v Makwanyane and Another 1995 (6) BCLR 665 (CC);  1995 (3) SA 391 (CC) at paras 328-330;  Hugo  above n 17 at para 41;  Prinsloo above n 17 at paras 31-33;  Ferreira v Levin NO and Others 1996 (1)  BCLR 1 (CC);  1996 (1) SA 984 (CC).','N'),(308,122,1,172,'South Africa|South African',451,'Constitutional Court','1995 (3) SA 391 (CC)',NULL,35,28,'phasised by the role accorded to it in section 36  of the Constitution which provides that:    “The rights in the Bill of Rights may be limited only in terms of law of general  ap